[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I am telling the truth in Christ (I am not lying!), for my conscience assures me"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " in the Holy Spirit – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " I have great sorrow and unceasing anguish in my heart."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For I could wish"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " that I myself were accursed – cut off from Christ – for the sake of my people,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " my fellow countrymen,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who are Israelites. To them belong"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the adoption as sons,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " the glory, the covenants, the giving of the law, the temple worship,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and the promises. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " To them belong the patriarchs,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " and from them,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " by human descent,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " came the Christ,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who is God over all, blessed forever!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Amen."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " It is not as though the word of God had failed. For not all those who are descended from Israel are truly Israel,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " nor are all the children Abraham’s true descendants; rather “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "through Isaac will your descendants be counted"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " This means"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it is not the children of the flesh"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " who are the children of God; rather, the children of promise are counted as descendants. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For this is what the promise declared:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "About a year from now"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " I will return and Sarah will have a son"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Not only that, but when Rebekah had conceived children by one man,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " our ancestor Isaac – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " even before they were born or had done anything good or bad (so that God’s purpose in election"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " would stand, not by works but by"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " his calling)"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it was said to her, “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "The older will serve the younger"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ",”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " just as it is written: “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Jacob I loved"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "but Esau I hated"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " What shall we say then? Is there injustice with God? Absolutely not! "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For he says to Moses: “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I will have mercy on whom I have mercy"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and I will have compassion on whom I have compassion"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So then,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it does not depend on human desire or exertion,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but on God who shows mercy. "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " For the scripture says to Pharaoh:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "For this very purpose I have raised you up, that I may demonstrate my power in you"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and that my name may be proclaimed in all the earth"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " So then,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " has mercy on whom he chooses to have mercy, and he hardens whom he chooses to harden."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " You will say to me then, “Why does he still find fault? For who has ever resisted his will?” "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But who indeed are you – a mere human being"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " – to talk back to God?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Does what is molded say to the molder"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Why have you made me like this?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Has the potter no right to make from the same lump of clay"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " one vessel for special use and another for ordinary use?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " But what if God, willing to demonstrate his wrath and to make known his power, has endured with much patience the objects"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of wrath"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " prepared for destruction?"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And what if he is willing to make known the wealth of his glory on the objects"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " of mercy that he has prepared beforehand for glory – "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " even us, whom he has called, not only from the Jews but also from the Gentiles? "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " As he also says in Hosea:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I will call those who were not my people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "My people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": " and I will call her who was unloved,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "My beloved"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "And in the very place"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "where it was said to them"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "You are not my people"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ","
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "there they will be called "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "‘"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "sons of the living God"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "’”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " And Isaiah cries out on behalf of Israel, “"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Though the number of the children"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "of Israel are as the sand of the sea"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "only the remnant will be saved"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "for the Lord will execute his sentence on the earth completely and quickly"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ".”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Just"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " as Isaiah predicted, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "If the Lord of armies"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "had not left us descendants"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "we would have become like Sodom"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and we would have resembled Gomorrah.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " What shall we say then? – that the Gentiles who did not pursue righteousness obtained it, that is, a righteousness that is by faith, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " but Israel even though pursuing"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " a law of righteousness"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " did not attain it."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " Why not? Because they pursued"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " it not by faith but (as if it were possible) by works."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " They stumbled over the stumbling stone,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": " just as it is written, "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "Look"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "I am laying in Zion a stone that will cause people to stumble"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "and a rock that will make them fall,"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "  "
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text_xref",
    "value": "yet the one who believes in him will not be put to shame."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]